reviews_data.review_text:
I stumbled on this coffee shop while trying to find a place to pass the time, my son has early dismal every Wednesday and it just makes sense to stay local!

Atmosphere: The decor is so chill and calming, Christian music (maverick city) played the entire 2.5-3 hours that I was there, the bar is open and your exposed to seeing their huge variety of syrups, tea, pastries and even a small ice cream freezer. The coffee is made right in front of you. Have a seat at the main bar, a couch, lounge chair or second bar close to the window. Outside, beautiful outside seating with lighting. There are bathrooms onsite, Parking is also open and easy.

Staff: The young ladies were so sweet, and you can tell that they take interest in their community/customers, they had many regulars come in and they would say their order before the customer even started ,haha, I've never seen that in person..just movies.

Selection: Hands down the largest and deliciously combined flavor selections! A variety of milk choices, The coffee is so smooth and fresh! I ordered a latte with white chocolate and caramel, oh my goodness, yumm! I also had their cinnamon roll, the cake was semi sweet, gooey and moist. The frosting was a little too rich for me but if you have a big sweet tooth, you'll enjoy it!

Work Friendly: The bar has charging ports and the shop has wifi!

I've found my hub on Wednesday!!

In a world where the rush of everyday life can be overwhelming, The Holy Grind provides a comforting escape.
